               <head>Jām-i Jahān'numā-'i Sāsānī (The World-Viewing Goblet of Sāsānī) and Life of Buddha translated from Rashīd al-Dīn (d. 1318).</head>
               <msContents>
                  <summary>A Persian treatise entitled <title>Jām-i Jahān'numā-'i Sāsānī</title> (The
                     World-Viewing Goblet of Sāsānī) bound together with the <title>History of Shākmūnī</title> or
                        <persName ref="http://viaf.org/viaf/54145602415401360869/"
                        key="person_54145602415401360869" role="subject"
                        change="#role-assignment #ids-cleanup">Gautama Buddha</persName> translated
                     from the <title>Jamī‘ al-Tavārīkh</title> (Compendium of Chronicles) of Rashīd
                     al-Dīn (d. 1318), the latter likely commissioned by <persName type="standard"
                        >John Staples Harriott</persName>, who once owned the Arabic manuscript now
                     held in the Khalili Collection.</summary>
               </msContents>
